WEBVTT

00:00:00.480 --> 00:00:04.400
<v Speaker 1>How would you say the situation in Spanish?

00:00:04.880 --> 00:00:06.240
<v Speaker 2>La situación.

00:00:06.240 --> 00:00:06.880
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:00:06.880 --> 00:00:09.120
<v Speaker 1>Yon is a feminine ending.

00:00:09.120 --> 00:00:13.280
<v Speaker 1>So the word takes la for the la situacion.

00:00:13.280 --> 00:00:14.960
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:00:14.320 --> 00:00:25.439
<v Speaker 1>Now in Spanish, adjectives, describing words, adjectives are words that describe like big or yellow or happy.

00:00:25.060 --> 00:00:29.860
<v Speaker 1>Words that we can put is in front of our adjectives describing words.

00:00:29.860 --> 00:00:34.100
<v Speaker 1>These words come after the noun they describe

00:00:34.360 --> 00:00:35.400
<v Speaker 1>in Spanish.

00:00:35.400 --> 00:00:42.040
<v Speaker 1>So instead of saying the global situation, for example, you say the situation global

00:00:42.160 --> 00:00:46.160
<v Speaker 1>There's a bit of flexibility for emphasis as well.

00:00:46.160 --> 00:00:50.480
<v Speaker 1>But the normal standard position is to come after the noun.

00:00:50.480 --> 00:00:53.840
<v Speaker 1>So how would you say the global situation?

00:00:54.580 --> 00:00:57.460
<v Speaker 2>La situación global.

00:00:57.460 --> 00:00:58.100
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:00:58.100 --> 00:00:59.940
<v Speaker 1>La situación global.

